/*
 * $Id: ChangeLog,v 1.3377 2004/08/30 16:55:11 mauriliolongo Exp $
 */

/* Use this format for the entry headers:
   YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM UTC[-|+]hhmm Your Full Name <your_email@address>
   For example:
   2002-12-01 23:12 UTC+0100 Foo Bar <foo.bar@foobar.org>
*/

2004-08-30 19:05 UTC+0200 Maurilio Longo <maurilio.longo@libero.it>
   * source/rtl/gtos2/gtos2.c
     ! since internal s_uiDispCount starts from 1, DispCount() should
       return it decremented by one

2004-08-30 18:53 UTC+0200 Maurilio Longo <maurilio.longo@libero.it>
   * ChangeLog
     * removed a few spurious characters on top. :)

2004-08-30 18:50 UTC+0200 Maurilio Longo <maurilio.longo@libero.it>
   * source/rtl/gtos2/gtos2.c
   * source/rtl/gtwin/gtwin.c
     ! fixed gt_Scroll() (hb_gt_Scroll() on gtos2.c) to fill screen with
       0xFF instead of 0x20 (clipper compatibility issue).

   /* NOTE: This fix should be applied to all other "console" type of
            terminal driver, but I don't know what happens when
            we fill a console with 0xFF on linux, so, for now, I've
            fixed only these two terminal drivers.
   */

2004-08-30 19:45 UTC+0530 Pritpal Bedi <pritpal@vouchcac.com>
  * xharbour/include/hbgtwvt.h
  * xharbour/include/wvtwin.ch
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwvt/gtwvt.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwvt/wvtcore.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwvt/wvtutils.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwvt/wvtclass.prg
  * xHarbour/tests/wvtgui.prg

    New functions, formatting, code cleanup, core rearrangement.

    Added the functionality to control the GUI elements when overlapped
    UI components are layered over the existing GUI components, and where
    array of GUI draw blocks has been forced for only that overlapped
    window, and when under this situation user clicks on some other
    window on the desktop and returns back to appln window. Earlier,
    under such scenario, the GUI elements drawn prior to the current paint
    block were erased. Now a special kind of buffering the current
    application screen is employed which is flushed back on the appln
    window when a WM_SETFOCUS or WM_KILLFOCUS is received by the
    appln followed by WM_PAINT. This is ultra fast and non-flickering
    protocol.

    The above behavior can be invoked with Wvt_SetGui( TRUE ). By default
    earlier behavior is retained just because many of you will be
    using pure console protocol thus eliminating the overhead.

    With this feature GTWVT is now capable of producing worry-free
    applications where no screen will be blurred when overlapped
    UI ( Alert(), AChoice(), Tbrowse() ) is invoked over existing
    GUI elements.

    +----------------------------------------------+
    :  +-----+                                     :
    :  : BMP :                                     :
    :  +-----+    +------------------------------+ :
    :             :                              : :
    :             :                              : :
    :             :                              : :
    :             :            BMP               : :
    :             :                              : :
    :             :                              : :
    :             :                              : :
    :             :                              : :
    :             +------------------------------+ :
    :                                              :
    +----------------------------------------------+

    The above is achieved with a set of WvtSetPaint() blocks.

    +----------------------------------------------+
    :  +-----+                                     :
    :  : BMP :                                     :
    :  +-----+    +------------------------------+ :
    :             :                              : :
    :             :                              : :
    :        +-----------------------------+     : :
    :        :         Alert Msg           :     : :
    :        +-----------------------------+     : :
    :             :                              : :
    :             :                              : :
    :             :                              : :
    :             +------------------------------+ :
    :                                              :
    +----------------------------------------------+

    Now an alert box is opened over it. That will be
    controlled by another set of paint blocks.

    Suppose user opens Outlook which partial covers the
    appln window. User closes Outlook and returns to appln.
    What will happen? The bitmaps drawn
    through first set of paint blocks are erased from the
    area covered by Outlook, though alert box will be displayed
    properly. You can well imagine how the blurred window will
    look-alike. With the current implementation, GTWVT takes
    care of it.

2004-08-30 07:51 UTC-0500 Paul Tucker <ptucker@sympatico.ca>
