2004-08-27 17:47 UTC+0200 Maurilio Longo <maurilio.longo@libero.it>
   * source/rtl/dbedit.prg
     ! put some extensions inside HB_COMPAT_C53
   * source/rtl/filesys.c
   * source/rtl/philes.c
   * source/ct/disk.c
     ! Fixed (or better, reverted/uniformed) handling of disk "name" (IDs).
       Inside xharbour rtl/vm disks are numbers from 0 to 25 and thers in not
       a value (number) which means "default disk".
       Default disk is ALWAYS the return value of a call to hb_fsCurDrv().

     /* NOTE: I've tested that all calls from code inside xharbour source tree
              to hb_fsDir/DirBuff/DirEx/DirBuffEx/ChDrv/IsDrv() do not
              pass a 0 value to say current disk but explicitly call
              hb_fsCurDrv().
              This was already correctly done in most places.
              I DID NOT test code inside contrib/ and tests/ so such code could
              require to be changed/corrected.
      */


