2004-08-14 12:04 UTC+0200 Maurilio Longo <maurilio.longo@libero.it>
  * source/rtl/tget.prg
    ! Small correction to latest fix, inside ::SetFocus() I forgot to
      explicitly set ::minus to .F. when editing a number

2004-08-14 11:48 UTC+0200 Maurilio Longo <maurilio.longo@libero.it>
  * source/rtl/tget.prg
    ! Incompatibility with clipper when ::buffer is filled with blanks and
      a decimal value is then inserted. See this sample:

      function main()

         LOCAL ncValore := 21.00
         LOCAL cPicture := "@ZE ##,###.##"
         LOCAL oGet :=  GetNew( 1 , 1 ,;
                       { |x| Iif( pCount() == 0 , ncValore , ncValore := x ) } , , cPicture )

         oGet:SetFocus()
         oGet:pos := oGet:DecPos + 1
         oGet:Clear   := .F.
         oGet:Changed := .T.
         oGet:Buffer := Transform( 0 , oGet:Picture )
         oGet:Insert("1")
         oGet:Assign()
         ? oGet:VarGet()
         ? oGet:Untransform()
         ? ncValore
     return

     Without this fix clipper prints .10 .10 .10 while xharbour  1 1 1,
     with this fix harbour prints .1 .1 .1

   ! ::setFocus() on clipper does not set ::minus to .T. when edited var
     has a negative value.

   /* NB: I think that tget.prg should not use exported iVars to keep
        internal values, for example ::minus is used in this way but
        clipper says that ::minus is .T. only when a "-" is pressed
        and ::buffer has a value of 0, every other change should reset
        it to .F.
        I have the impression that other iVars could not strictly follow
        clipper behaviour.
   */

