  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwvt/wvtutils.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwvt/wvtclass.prg
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwvt/wvtpaint.prg
    Fixed compiler warnings.

  * xharbour/include/hbgtwvt.h
    + s_.hDlgModeless slot to hold one modeless dialog window handle.

  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtwvt/gtwvt.c
    Optimization as to correct rectangle in terms fo rows/cols to be
    painted in WM_PAINT message. Earlier it was painting 2 rows and two
    cols more than required, i.e., { 4,4,10,20 } -> { 3,3,11,21 }
    Due care has been taken if the painting is not initiated by any
    GtWvt function, then entire region is painted.

    + static BOOL CALLBACK hb_wvt_gtDlgProcModeless()
    + HB_EXPORT HWND hb_wvt_gtCreateDialog()
      Started logic to handle MODELESS dialogs from within the Gtwvt.

  * xharbour/tests/wvtgui.prg
    Fixed WvtLines() to respect window's focus change behavior.

  * xharbour/source/vm/hvm.c
    + HB_FUNC( HB_NOSTARTUPWINDOW )
      Earlier, if no startup window was required, GtWvt.lib needed
      to be compiled with -D__WVT_NOSHOW_STARTUP__ cflag.
      This behavior is now changed. Now you need to
      REQUEST Hb_NoStartupWindow
      which will force the startup window to be HIDDEN which can be
      brought in view with Wvt_ShowWindow( S_RESTORE ).

2004-07-22 18:55 UTC+0300 Phil Krylov <phil a t newstar.rinet.ru>
  * source/rtl/filesys.c
    * Fixed some warnings.

