2004-07-21 13:58 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron at xharbour.com>
  * source/compiler/harbour.c
  * source/compiler/harbour.sly
    - Defed out hb_compSequenceFinish() - this optimization did not take into account Jump Optimizatios
      and thus created a GPF trap. Adding a "rewind" of Jump Data is more complex than might seemed to be.

2004-07-21 17:10 UTC+0530 Pritpal Bedi <pritpal@vouchcac.com>
  * GTWVT - Needed Approach
    Now if GtWvt.lib is compiled with -D__WVT_NOSHOW_STARTUP__,
    then the appln window is not visible until Wvt_ShowWindow( SW_RESTORE )
    is called. This has been necessary to avoid black window being visible
    prior to setting the fonts and size desired.
    Moreover, there may be a need ( sometimes ) that appln window
    should not be visible until desired.

2004-07-21 16:45 UTC+0530 Pritpal Bedi <pritpal@vouchcac.com>
  * xharbour/include/inkey.ch
    + #define K_NCMOUSEMOVE  1016
      Posted to WindProc when mouse hovers on Non-Client area of a Window.

  * xharbour/include/wvtwin.ch
    + #define SW_* constants
      These constants contol Windows current state and can be used
      as Wvt_ShowWindow( SW_HIDE ) ( SW_RESTORE ) etc.

